The high selectivity and specificity with the excellent fluorescence restoration phenomenon of PLP@l-Cyst-Mn-ZnS QDs towards ATP encourage us to investigate the sensitivity [55]. Fig. 6

                        a showed the changes in the fluorescence spectra of PLP@l-Cyst-Mn-ZnS QDs upon gradual incremental addition of ATP from 0 M to 8.9 × 10−6 M. The fluorescence intensity at 603 nm was enhanced with the incremental addition of ATP. Form the calibration curve (Fig. 6
                        b), the detection limit was estimated as 1.4 × 10−7 M. The estimated detection limit of PLP@l-Cyst-Mn-ZnS QDs towards ATP is comparable with the reported probes (
                           Table S2
                        ). ATP is an important energy source for metabolism, intracellular signaling and many of biochemical reactions [32,56]. Therefore, efforts have been made to monitor ATP in real human serum and plasma samples. The ATP quantification by PLP@l-Cyst-Mn-ZnS QDs in spiked serum and plasma samples showed good recoveries (Table 2
                        ), which showed the practical applicability of PLP@l-Cyst-Mn-ZnS QDs for detecting ATP.
